nt of the colorado springs hispanic chamber of commerce, a board member of the colorado springs greater chamber of commerce and united way board of trustees and executive committee member and a co-chair of the springs community action plan. rivera was first elected to an at large city council seat in april of 1997 and re-elected again in april of 1999. in april 2001, he was elected by his city council colleagues to serve as vice mayor for a two year term. rivera has worked as a financial advisor for more than 20 years advising business owners, retirees, non-profits and young families on a range of financial issues. rivera and his wife lynn reside in colorado springs.</p></span>



